SIMPLE: understudy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Understudy
<hw>Un"der*stud`y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos>
<fld>(Theater)</fld> <def>To study, as another actor's part, in order to
be his substitute in an emergency; to study another actor's
part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Understudy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Understudy
<hw>Un"der*stud`y</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who studies another's
part with a view to assuming it in an emergency.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undersuit</ent>⟦br⟧
